1. Yesterday, the US Bitcoin spot ETF had a net outflow of US$64.1 million, and BlackRock IBIT had no inflow/outflow of funds;
2. pump.fun has deposited 2,345,499 SOLs, equivalent to US$473 million, with Kraken so far;
3. Nic Carter: The era of Meme coins as fair trading opportunities is over, and regulators may take action against insider trading;
4. Tether launches innovative financing solution TradeFi, using blockchain to promote global trade;
5. OKX: Mining software Bom is suspected of malicious behavior, and potential risk addresses need to transfer assets as soon as possible;
6. A user sniped 107,212 PAIN and lost US$436,000 to clear the position;
7. Aptos research director accused Monad of plagiarism, Monad co-founder denied it and said "I was developing it when you were still wearing diapers";
8. Nexus Orchestrator is dealing with a large number of requests and DoS Attack, the team will try its best to keep the network unobstructed;
9. Metaplanet increased its holdings by 68.69 BTC, and its current BTC holdings account for 0.01% of the total supply;
10. Walrus will launch the mainnet in March and launch WAL tokens: a total of 5 billion, 10% for Walrus User Drop;
11. Musk: Grok 3 will be open to everyone for free in the short term;
12. Vitalik: The future development of Ethereum can focus on reducing dependence on centralized intermediaries and ensuring that open participation remains intact;
13. StarkWare co-founder: Vitalik has led Ethereum through many crises, and it will be safe and sound.
